---
description: Core Axiomurgy invariants and workflow
alwaysApply: true
---

- Preserve Axiomurgy's core model: spells are explicit graphs executed under capability, policy, approval, and witness constraints.
- Keep side effects reviewable. Do not bypass approval or rollback semantics for convenience.
- Prefer incremental patches over rewrites.
- Before finishing, run `python -m pytest -q`.
- If runtime behavior changed, also run `bash scripts/smoke.sh`.
- Keep docs, examples, and code in sync.
- When changing versions, update version strings and user-facing docs together.
